<PubmedArticle><MedlineCitation Status="Publisher" Owner="NLM"><PMID Version="1">41135602</PMID><DateRevised><Year>2025</Year><Month>12</Month><Day>29</Day></DateRevised><Article PubModel="Print-Electronic"><Journal><ISSN IssnType="Electronic">1543-2742</ISSN><JournalIssue CitedMedium="Internet"><PubDate><Year>2025</Year><Month>Oct</Month><Day>23</Day></PubDate></JournalIssue><Title>International journal of sport nutrition and exercise metabolism</Title><ISOAbbreviation>Int J Sport Nutr Exerc Metab</ISOAbbreviation></Journal><ArticleTitle>UCI Sports Nutrition Project: Performance Nutrition for Sprint and Endurance Track Cycling.</ArticleTitle><Pagination><StartPage>1</StartPage><EndPage>12</EndPage><MedlinePgn>1-12</MedlinePgn></Pagination><ELocationID EIdType="doi" ValidYN="Y">10.1123/ijsnem.2025-0043</ELocationID><Abstract><AbstractText>Track cycling is a unique discipline whereby events take place on a velodrome using fixed-gear bicycles. Events cover a spectrum of durations ranging from &lt;11&#xa0;s through to &#x223c;60&#xa0;min. Therefore, diverse and specialized physiological attributes are required to meet the specific demands of competition. Nutrition has a fundamental role in optimizing athlete performance through maintaining overall health, fueling training to develop the required physiological characteristics for success and enabling athletes to meet the energy demands of competition. This review will focus on how nutrition can be optimized to best support the training periodization and competition requirements and provide practical recommendations on fueling strategies for track cycling.</AbstractText></Abstract><AuthorList CompleteYN="Y"><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Stanley</LastName><ForeName>Jamie</ForeName><Initials>J</Initials><Identifier Source="ORCID">0000-0003-0000-8777</Identifier><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>South Australian Sports Institute, Adelaide, SA, Australia.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>AusCycling-Performance, Adelaide, SA, Australia.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>University of South Australia, Adelaide, SA, Australia.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Leo</LastName><ForeName>Peter</ForeName><Initials>P</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>AusCycling-Performance, Adelaide, SA, Australia.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Department of Sports Science, University of Innsbruck, Innsbruck, Austria.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Haakonssen</LastName><ForeName>Eric</ForeName><Initials>E</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>AusCycling-Performance, Adelaide, SA, Australia.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Leckey</LastName><ForeName>Jill J</ForeName><Initials>JJ</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>South Australian Sports Institute, Adelaide, SA, Australia.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author></AuthorList><Language>eng</Language><PublicationTypeList><PublicationType UI="D016428">Journal Article</PublicationType></PublicationTypeList><ArticleDate DateType="Electronic"><Year>2025</Year><Month>10</Month><Day>23</Day></ArticleDate></Article><MedlineJournalInfo><Country>United States</Country><MedlineTA>Int J Sport Nutr Exerc Metab</MedlineTA><NlmUniqueID>100939812</NlmUniqueID><ISSNLinking>1526-484X</ISSNLinking></MedlineJournalInfo><CitationSubset>IM</CitationSubset><KeywordList Owner="NOTNLM"><Keyword MajorTopicYN="N">competition demands</Keyword><Keyword MajorTopicYN="N">fueling</Keyword><Keyword MajorTopicYN="N">periodization</Keyword><Keyword MajorTopicYN="N">velodrome</Keyword></KeywordList></MedlineCitation><PubmedData><History><PubMedPubDate PubStatus="received"><Year>2025</Year><Month>3</Month><Day>12</Day></PubMedPubDate><PubMedPubDate PubStatus="revised"><Year>2025</Year><Month>5</Month><Day>14</Day></PubMedPubDate><PubMedPubDate PubStatus="accepted"><Year>2025</Year><Month>6</Month